Basic Installation
==================

The simplest way to compile this package is:

  1. `cd' to the directory containing the package's confgiguration sources
	 code and you can modify then to customize the library for you personal 
	 use. For example, by default the library use a free url to get the 
	 timestamp.

  2. `cd' to the directory containing the package's source code and type 
	 `make' to compile the package.

  3. Type `make install' to install the programs and any data files and
     documentation. Due to multiple compilation may occur for differents
	 profiles of configuration, installation directories are the same 
	 /lib and /include in the containing directory of the package.

